{{Infobox football biography | name = Dwight McNeil | image = Dwight McNeil controls the ball.jpg | caption = McNeil playing for Burnley | image_size = | fullname = Dwight James Matthew McNeil<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/84136 |title=Squads for 2016/17 Premier League confirmed|website=Premier League|accessdate=16 May 2018|date=1 September 2016}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1999|11|22|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/dwight-mcneil-257647/ |title=Dwight McNeil|website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=16 May 2018}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Rochdale]], England | height = | position = [[Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] | clubnumber = 31 | youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2014 | youthclubs1 = [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] | youthyears2 = 2014–2018 | youthclubs2 = [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] | years1 = 2018– | clubs1 = [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] | caps1 = 12 | goals1 = 1 | club-update = 21:37, 27 February 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = }} '''Dwight James Matthew McNeil''' (born 22 November 1999) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] / [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].
==Career== [[File:Dwight McNeil looks to take a Montpellier player on.jpg|alt=Dwight McNeil looks to take a Montpellier player on in pre-season for Burnley|thumb|Dwight McNeil looks to take a Montpellier player on in pre-season for Burnley]] Born in [[Rochdale]], [[Greater Manchester]], McNeil started his career in the youth system at [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] before he signed for the [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] Academy in 2014.<ref name="BFC">{{cite web |url=https://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/teams/u18-team/2nd-year-scholar/dwight-mcneill/ |title=Burnley profile |website=Burnley F.C. |accessdate=16 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180517152707/https://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/teams/u18-team/2nd-year-scholar/dwight-mcneill/ |archive-date=2018-05-17 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> In July 2016 he was rewarded with a two-year scholarship and was a regular member of the under-18 squad and occasionally played for the Development Squad.<ref name="BFC"/> In February 2018, he travelled with the first team squad for the [[Premier League]] game against [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] but failed to make the match-day squad.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/sport/16037402.Clarets_youngster_McNeil_wants_more_after_first_team_taster/|title=Clarets youngster McNeil wants more after first team taster|website=Lancashire Telegraph|date=21 February 2018 |accessdate=16 May 2018|first=Tyrone|last=Marshall}}</ref> On 10 April 2018, following the end of his scholarship, he signed a professional two-year contract with the option of a third year in the clubs favour.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/sport/football/burnley_fc/news/16149695.Burnley_prospects_sign_professional_deals/|title=Burnley prospects sign professional deals|website=Lancashire Telegraph|date=10 April 2018 |accessdate=16 May 2018|first=Tyrone|last=Marshall}}</ref> On 13 May 2018 he made his first team debut in the final match of the [[2017–18 Burnley F.C. season|2017–18]] season when he replaced [[Aaron Lennon]] as a late substitute in the 2–1 home defeat to [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]].<ref name=sb1718/> McNeil scored his first goal for the club in a 2–0 home win against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] on 30 December 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46663364|title=Burnley manager Sean Dyche says a couple of "big decisions" in his team selection contributed to a vital win over West Ham at Turf Moor.}}</ref>
==Personal life== McNeil's father, [[Matty McNeil|Matty]], played in the [[English Football League|Football League]] for [[Macclesfield Town F.C.|Macclesfield Town]] and [[Stockport County F.C.|Stockport County]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/news/2018/december/dream-day-for-goalscorer-mcneil/|title=Dream Day For Goalscorer McNeil|website=Burnley F.C.|date=31 December 2018 |accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref>
