{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Use British English|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox football biography | name= Dan Agyei | image = | caption = | fullname = Daniel Ebenezer Kwasi Agyei<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.efl.com/news/article/2016/efl-club-retained-and-released-lists-published-3151313.aspx|publisher=[[English Football League]]|accessdate=22 August 2016|date=23 June 2016|title=EFL: Club retained and released lists published}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1997|06|01}}<ref name="11v11">{{cite web |title=Dan Agyei |url=http://www.11v11.com/players/dan-agyei-248936/|work=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises|accessdate=16 January 2016}}</ref> | birth_place = [[Royal Borough of Kingston upon Thames|Kingston upon Thames]], England | height = {{convert|1.83|m|order=flip}}<ref name="11v11"/> | position = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]] / [[Winger (football)|Winger]] | currentclub = [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] | clubnumber = 32 | youthyears1 = 2013–2015 | youthclubs1 = [[AFC Wimbledon]] | years1 = 2015– | clubs1 = [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] | caps1 = 3 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2016–2017 | clubs2 = → [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] (loan) | caps2= 16 | goals2 = 4 | years3 = 2017–2018 | clubs3 = → [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] (loan) | caps3 = 18 | goals3 = 4 | years4 = 2018 | clubs4 = → [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] (loan) | caps4 = 9 | goals4 = 0 | club-update = 19:08, 7 May 2018 (UTC) }} '''Daniel Ebenezer Kwasi Agyei''' (born 1 June 1997) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]].
==Career==
===Burnley ===
Agyei came through the ranks at [[AFC Wimbledon]], scoring 35 goals for the club's under-21 team in the 2014–15 season to draw the attention of a host of top clubs, reportedly including [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]], [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] and [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{cite web|title=West Ham take Wimbledon's Daniel Agyei on trial amid Chelsea interest |publisher=Squawka|date=2 July 2015|url= http://www.squawka.com/news/west-ham-take-wimbledons-daniel-agyei-on-trial-amid-chelsea-interest/410043}}</ref> Agyei eventually signed for [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], on a long-term contract to initially play for the club's development squad.<ref>{{cite web|title=Clarets Complete Agyei Signing |publisher=Burnley FC |date=4 August 2015|url= http://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/news/article/clarets-swoop-to-sign-agyei-2578923.aspx}}</ref>
After impressing for Burnley's development squad in the 2015/16 season and making his senior Burnley debut in a pre-season friendly against [[Bradford City]], Agyei was made available for a loan move by manager [[Sean Dyche]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Burnley striker Dan Agyei set for loan spell but will he be winging his way to Coventry City? | publisher=Coventry Telegraph | date=3 August 2016 | url= http://www.coventrytelegraph.net/sport/football/burnley-striker-dan-agyei-set-11694735}}</ref> [[Coventry City]] beat off competition from several clubs in League One and the Championship to secure the loan signing of Agyei on a five-month loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dan Agyei: Coventry City sign Burnley striker on loan |publisher=BBC Football |date=18 August 2016|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37115109}}</ref> Agyei was handed the number 9 shirt by Coventry City manager [[Tony Mowbray]] upon arrival at the [[Ricoh Arena]].<ref>{{cite web|title=SIGNING: Coventry City FC confirm the signing of Daniel Agyei from Burnley on a five-month loan deal |publisher=CCFC |date=18 August 2016|url= http://www.ccfc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/signing-daniel-ageyi-burnley-coventry-city-3256661.aspx}}</ref>
Agyei made his professional league debut against Bradford City on 20 August 2016, handing Coventry City the lead with his first goal in professional league football in a 3–1 defeat at Valley Parade.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bradford City 3–1 Coventry City |publisher=BBC Football |date=20 August 2016|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37067578}}</ref> He then scored his second goal of the season in a 2–0 home win against Rochdale.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37664401|title=Coventry City 2–0 Rochdale|date=2016-10-22|newspaper=BBC Sport|language=en-GB|accessdate=2016-10-25}}</ref> In October 2016, he scored Coventry's fastest ever goal at the [[Ricoh Arena]] after just 19.5 seconds to set a new record in the 3–1 victory over [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] in the [[EFL Trophy]].<ref>{{cite web|title=RECORD: Daniel Agyei scores the fastest ever goal at the Ricoh during Checkatrade Trophy win|publisher=Coventry City FC |date=7 October 2016|url=http://www.ccfc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/record-dan-agyei-fastest-goal-ricoh-coventry-northampton-071016-3351901.aspx}}</ref> In January 2017, he returned to Burnley following the expiration of his loan, he made a total of 19 appearances for the Sky Blues, netting five goals.<ref>{{cite web|title=NEWS: Striker Daniel Agyei returns to parent club Burnley after Sky Blues loan spell|publisher=Coventry City FC |date=3 January 2017|url=http://www.ccfc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/dan-agyei-loan-spell-burnley-coventry-city-3499161.aspx}}</ref>
He made his debut on 12 March 2017 coming on in the 88th minute replacing [[Scott Arfield]] against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].{{cn|date=July 2018}}
On 31 August 2017, Agyei joined [[EFL League One|League One]] club [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] on loan until January 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41118044 |title=Walsall: Burnley forward Daniel Agyei and Bury winger Zeli Ismail on loan |publisher=BBC Sport |date=31 August 2017 |accessdate=1 September 2017 }}</ref> He made a total of twenty-one appearances in all competitions scoring five goals before returning to Burnley.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uptheclarets.com/agyei-back-at-burnley |title=Agyei back at Burnley |publisher=UpTheClarets |date=4 January 2018 |accessdate=9 January 2018 }}</ref>
On 18 January 2018, Agyei joined [[EFL League One|League One]] club [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] on loan until the end of the 2017–18 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.blackpoolfc.co.uk/news/2018/january/blackpool-bring-in-agyei/ |title=Blackpool: Blackpool Bring In Agyei |publisher=Blackpool F.C. |date=18 January 2018 |accessdate=18 January 2018}}</ref>
